Version compatibility
Version compatibility
For all new features enabled from 1.2.5:
List of all "baseline" & "enhanced" features ishere;
Transaction flow for new features, with corresponding feature id, ishere;
BNPs & SNPs may prioritize & enable one or more features as per their business requirements;
BNP & SNP will publish the list of features enabled for mutual featurediscovery;
Context.version, for the corresponding APIs, will be set to "1.2.5";
Version 1.2.5 will be considered an update to version 1.2.0 & hence will be fully backward compatible with version 1.2.0 (but not with 1.1.0):
Each new feature will be incrementally layered on the base version 1.2.0;
"1.2.5" version of these APIs will be fully backward compatible with "1.2.0" version of the same APIs:
BNP sends 1.2.0 API request => some SNPs may send 1.2.0 response, other SNPs may send 1.2.5 response;
BNP sends 1.2.5 API request => some SNPs may send 1.2.0 response, other SNPs may send 1.2.5 response;
BNP sending 1.2.5 request must also include the list of features supported;
SNP supporting 1.2.5 features may enable business workflows for supported features based on mutual feature discovery;
NPs may have version check enabled for "1.2.*";
Baseline (pre-order)
Full catalog refresh
Search request is always broadcast through the gateway so that all NPs who have registered for the specific domain, in the search request, are notified;
Full catalog response will be sent directly from the SNPs to the BNP, from which the search request was received through the gateway;
The SNP should send the full catalog response in GZIP-compressed format to support large payloads over the APIs. The callback response must include the HTTP headerContent-Encoding: gzipto indicate compression;
/search (by city)
/search will be used to communicate the intent for a full (or incremental) catalog refresh;
BNP can optionally refresh catalogs for a city bysub-category, e.g. for Grocery (ONDC:RET10), catalog can be refreshed separately for each sub-category:
e.g. for "Bakery, Cakes & Dairy", Context.domain="ONDC:RET10", category.id = "Bakery, Cakes & Dairy";
distributed search i.e. by category will also allow differential buyer finder fee for different sub-categories in a domain;
however, this will not be possible for categories, such as F&B, where no such sub-categories are defined;
Buyer NP (BNP) will also publish the static terms fortransaction level contractthrough this API;
