3. Store reopening
following states can be passed for a store in the catalog refresh:
open- open an already enabled store:
using full / incremental catalog refresh;
using time.label="open", time.timestamp = event timestamp;
store will be shown as open after BNP processes the incremental refresh;
after the store reopens, it will default to the normal store timings;
if used for disabled store, BNP may NACK with error code 20004;
close- close an already enabled store:
using full / incremental catalog refresh;
using time.label="close", time.timestamp = event timestamp, time.range.start = start datetime for closure, time.range.end is optional;
if time.range.end is not passed, the store will remain closed until it is marked as open in a subsequent catalog refresh (incremental or full);
any subsequent incremental catalog refresh that happens, when the store remains closed, may have updates for the items for that store. BNP should process this so that the updated items are visible when the store reopens;
any subsequent full catalog refresh that happens, when the store remains closed, will have the store marked as closed, along with the other details that are a part of the full catalog;
enable- for activation of store by BNP or for updating other information including serviceability, items, store timing, etc:
using full catalog refresh (for now);
using time.label="enable", time.timestamp = event timestamp;
store timings using provider.timing;
disable- for soft-delete of store by BNP:
using full / incremental catalog refresh;
using time.label="disable", time.timestamp = event timestamp;
