Rules for order confirmation
/confirm and /on_confirm calls are idempotent;
BNP creates the order id which will be unique across the network;
in response to /confirm from BNP, SNP sends /on_confirm with the same order_id;
BNP sends /confirm, SNP validates[628]order:
validation successful, SNP responds with ACK:
SNP creates order (preferably with internal state to indicate order is being processed), but should not forward to merchant for processing & fulfillment;
validation not successful, SNP responds with NACK with error code 31002 (order validation failure):
after BNP receives NACK, they should cancel the order withreason code999 (order cancelled because of order confirmation failure);
if this order is passed in subsequent API calls (/confirm, /status, /cancel, /update, etc.), SNP returns NACK with error code 30018 (order not found);
SNP may also respond with NACK due to other internal errors (http 504, retriable error code 31001):
BNP should retry[629]/confirm:
if after the retry interval, BNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 999;
if BNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK or /on_confirm, they should retry /confirm (same as above).
if within retry interval, BNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK or /on_confirm, they should cancel the order with reason code 999;
SNP sends /on_confirm, BNP validates[630]order:
validation successful, BNP responds with ACK:
SNP forwards order to merchant for processing & fulfillment;
validation not successful, BNP responds with NACK with error code 23002 (order validation failure):
after SNP receives NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 998 (order cancelled because of order confirmation failure) & push the status change to BNP;
if this order (with cancellation state & reason code) is passed in subsequent API calls (/on_confirm, /on_status, /on_cancel, /on_update), BNP responds with ACK;
BNP may also NACK due to internal errors (http 504/503, retriable error code 23001):
SNP should retry[631]/on_confirm. If after the retry interval, SNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 998;
if order is passed in subsequent API calls within the retry window (/status, /track, /cancel, /update), SNP responds with current order state along with error code 31003 to indicate order processing in progress;
if order is passed in subsequent API calls after cancellation (/status, /cancel, /update), SNP sends response with order state as cancelled;
if SNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK for /on_confirm, they should retry /on_confirm:
if after the retry interval, SNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 998;
Baseline (post-order)
Return
Scenario 1 - Part cancel by merchant
Cancel of item(s) can only be initiated if fulfillment state is "Pending";
Separate fulfillment is created for the cancellation and the item & quantity assigned to it; this fulfillment also has associated details such as cancellation reason code, quote trail;
For part cancel of dynamic item for specific quantity:
the base item and customizations should be cancelled in the same proportion and the quote updated accordingly, i.e. SNP cancels the dynamic item and sets the quantity & total price to 0 for all item & customization components;
individual item or customization components can’t be part-cancelled;
if either of the above is not followed, BNP should NACK the /on_update with error code 22508;
For merchant part-cancel:
BNP may send NACK with error code 22501 (if the buyer does not accept part fill for the order);
In this case, the SNP will be required to rollback this part cancel request and cancel the full order;
Updated quote is provided by the SNP at the refund trigger state ("Liquidated", "Return_Picked", "Cancelled") and the BNP can calculate the amount of refund from the quote trail;
