Rules for return
Order may be updated, at its terminal state ("Completed"), for the following:
with order.state = "Completed", there may be return of 1 or more items, within the return window for these items:
For every return request, a separate fulfillment is created to track the return request and the refund associated with the return request;
Response for part-return should have exactly the same number of items for which return is requested;
Order value (quote.price.value) cannot increase through /on_update:
if order value decreases, it should be due to decrease in item quantity (quote.breakup[]."@ondc/org/item_quantity".count) for "@ondc/org/title_type" of "item";
quote trail is immutable, after it is added to the order at the refund trigger point;
/on_update (solicited or unsolicited) should be called:
whenever there is change in the order details (e.g. due to buyer return);
whenever there is only a status change, an unsolicited /on_status call should be made;
/on_update should return the same information as /on_status i.e. the audit trail for items (including returns, cancels processed or in-progress), the current state of order items & fulfillment, order quote and breakup, settlement trail (if available);
Batching of order updates & status changes should not be done;
Cancellation
/cancel
If cancellation_reason_id is invalid (i.e. doesn’t exist or isn’t applicable for BNP), SNP can NACK /cancel with error code 30012;
Cancellation can be initiated by BNP on fulfillment TAT breach with cancellation_reason_id "006" and with the appropriate fulfillment id as shown:
if SNP determines that fulfillment TAT is not breached, they can NACK /cancel with error code 30014;
